{
  "stem": "11801.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When someone sends a child away in this country-- say, summer camp or to sleep over, I mean, you make sure that, you know, the camp is a good one, that it has a telephone, that it has proper medical attention, that it's clean and that the children are well fed, that they are properly taken care of, that they're-- you know, that they have positive experiences.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, my parents knew nothing, nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They didn't know where I would be going.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All they knew was that it was better to leave than to stay and that no matter what happened on the other side of the border, it would be better for us, for my brother and myself, than staying in, in, in Germany.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was my mother who was really the force in, in our household.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she had a street smartness about her that helped her along many times, including at that time when she, when she understood the importance of sending us away before the war broke out, that she saw the writing on the wall.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, on one hand, they waited much too long.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They should have left in '33, '34, '35.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They didn't do it because, like so many other Germans, they were staunch Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They-- my mother lost a brother in the First World War, you know, had fought for the Kaiser and for the, for Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were-- I think they were Germans first and Jews second.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they simply did not believe that, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that Hitler was serious about his threats.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, many, many did believe it and left, fortunately, but too many did not.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
